ft, a trauma surgeon who unexpectedly commits suicide, a wounded murderer, a man chased across the New Mexico desert by a heat-seeking missile. At times surreal, at times lyrical, at times brutal and terrifying, The Blood of Strangers is a literary work that emerges from one of the most dramatic specialties of modern medicine. This deeply affecting first book has been described by one early reader as "the best doctor collection I have seen since William Carlos Williams's The Doctor Stories."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEmergency medicinevPopular works. 0aEmergency medicine. 0aHospitalsxEmergency servicesvPopular works. 0aHospitalsxEmergency services. 7aMEDICAL / Health Care Delivery.2bisacsh  aaccidents.  aanthology.  ablood.  acareer.  acollection of stories.  adisease.  aemergency medicine.  aemergency rooms.  aemotional.  aer physicians.  afast paced.  afirsthand accounts.  ahealthcare.  ahuman struggles.  aillness.  ainjury.  alife and death.  aliterary nonfiction.  alyrical essays.  amedical professionals.  amedical world.  amemoirs.  amodern medicine.  aneurosurgeons.  anew mexico.  anonfiction stories.  apatients and doctors.  aretrospective.  atrauma surgeons.  avignettes.  avisceral.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052021863540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095072640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520950726423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520950726/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY